**Putin humiliated as Ukraine saboteurs launch surprise assault deep in Russian territory**
Approximately 300 Ukrainian soldiers launched a surprise cross-border attack into Russian territory on Tuesday, reaching as far as six miles (10 km) inside Russia, according to Moscow. The attack, which was bolstered by 11 tanks and more than 20 armored fighting vehicles, was initiated at 8am and persisted throughout the day between the border villages of Nikolayevo-Daryino and Oleshnya in Russia's Kursk region. Russian claims of successfully repelling the incursion were quickly proved false, with reports from Russian military bloggers and social media footage indicating the Ukrainian attack was highly significant. Andrii Kovalenko, head of the anti-disinformation department at Ukraine's National Security and Defense Council, acknowledged the attack's occurrence, suggesting it had not been fully defeated. Military analysts suggest the attack could aim to divert Russian forces to defend an underactive part of the front since spring 2022 and boost Ukrainian morale. However, critics in Ukraine argue such assaults yield no long-term military advantage.
