**Ukraine's War Effort: Challenges and Prospects**
According to military expert Pavel Narozhny, Ukraine's army will have to continue defending on the Donbass front for a long time, while in the Zaporizhzhia and Kherson regions, the Ukrainian Armed Forces will be able to launch an offensive and liberate occupied territories from Russia. Narozhny listed the current problems in the Ukrainian Armed Forces, including the slow pace of mobilization, the slow delivery of promised weapons, and the threat of Russian aviation. He noted that the flow of mobilized personnel will be felt in October 2024, and that Ukraine lacks the ability to shoot down Russian planes. The expert also stated that the transfer of F-16s is taking too long and will not happen before the end of 2024. He predicted that the situation on the front will be difficult, with the possibility of Ukrainian forces retreating and losing territory. However, he believes that by spring 2025, Ukraine may be able to regain the initiative, with the possibility of launching an offensive, striking at Russia, and liberating occupied territories.
